pread to other planets though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zentrander>Zentrander</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Orion Commander</span><br>  Posts: 252<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/29/03 7:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=135.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> but evolution is a natural process, which we want to continue, and would even facilitate through stellar colonization...extinction should be avoided, and is not a natural function of a species seeking to expand its biosphere. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 778<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/29/03 9:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=135.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://image1ex.villagephotos.com/extern/935754.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: hmm</span><hr size=1> I only hope that evolution continues in the right direction.  As someone else mentioned on this board, we might end up evolving into idiots.  Human cloning could throw an interesting twist into evolution.  I like the idea of people procreating naturally since we're more likely to give rise to people with varied talents that way.  Imagine if Einstein's parents decided to just clone themselves instead of having children the natural way for instance.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td 